main event: A UFO sighting involving a large white, circular object was tracked by ground radar and visually observed over Minneapolis, Minnesota on October 28, 1955.
interesting points: The UFO was tracked by both air and ground radar,The object was estimated to be 15,000 feet high,The UFO was observed for a duration of 21 minutes but was at a high speed for only 15 to 20 seconds,Initial tracking estimated the object going at 1,500 knots, The sighting is inconclusive with possibilities including a balloon or aircraft.
witness description: Pilot observed object during two passes, gave no description.
